7 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING THE ALLOCATION OF EXCESS LOTTERY REVENUE
8 TO SCHOOLS; PROVIDING FOR QUARTERLY DISTRIBUTIONS TO SCHOOLS BASED ON A PER-
9 QUALITY-EDUCATOR FORMULA; PROVIDING A STATUTORY APPROPRIATION; REVISING ELIGIBLE
10 USES OF A SCHOOL'S FLEXIBILITY FUND; AMENDING SECTIONS 20-9-543, 23-7-202, AND 23-7-402,
11 MCA; AND PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE.”
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
14
15 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Distribution of lottery revenues. (1) The office of public instruction shall
16 distribute lottery revenues received pursuant to 23-7-402 on a quarterly basis and within 30 days of receiving
17 the funds. The funds must be distributed to schools on a per-quality-educator basis, with the amount to be
18 distributed to each district calculated by dividing the total funds available for distribution by the total number of
19 quality educators, as defined in 20-4-502, employed by each school district in the state in the immediately
20 preceding school fiscal year.
21 (2) A school district receiving funds under this section shall deposit the funds in its flexibility fund
22 established under 20-9-543.
23
